Lola: Saw posts that there have been some new docs.

Florian: Been working on security. Threat modeling in march. See threat modeling post that is merged on MDN. Part of "Security on the Web" section. Reshaping security tree of MDN; focusing mostly on attacks, such as man in the middle, supply chain attacks, etc. Then worked on defenses that help counter the attacks. Third part is authentication, such as passwords, multifactor like passwords, passkeys. Last month we looked at threaat modeling. This is not "a latest feature"; not a web doc, but rather a risk assessment process. slightly different from our usual work. Demonstrated and explained the threat model section of MDN. goal to make threat modeling more approachable for the average web developer; not just something for security experts

